The Commission will continue to hear evidence relating to allegations of corruption at the Passenger Rail Agency of South Africa (PRASA) from the former Group Chief Executive Officer Lucky Montana.   JOHANNESBURG - Former Prasa CEO Lucky Montana is expected back in the hot seat at the State Capture Commission. He's continuing his testimony from last week. Montana said his demise was as a result of him standing up to certain unnamed ANC heavyweights, who he accuses of collapsing Prasa. READ: Lucky Montana slams Zondo Commission During Montana's tenure at the Passenger Rail Agency, he claims up to 85 percent of our trains ran. What he says took Prasa 10 years to build under his leadership, was destroyed in a mere three years. He says only about 20 percent of trains now run.